This paper deals with the problem of privacy-preserving data synthesis, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as the paper presents a new criterion for privacy guarantee that does not depend on the background knowledge of an adversary. The second likely category is cs.DB (Databases), as the paper presents mechanisms to generate synthetic datasets with similar statistical properties to the input data and the same format. The third likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper demonstrates the efficiency of the generative technique on a large dataset with respect to various statistical analysis and machine learning measures. The fourth likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper presents a method for generating synthetic data that preserves the utility of original data. The fifth likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper deals with the problem of releasing full data records while preserving privacy.
